<task id="080" project="ai-procedure-quality-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Create .claude/skills/procedure-quality-audit/SKILL.md</title>
    <phase>5</phase>
    <stream>cadence</stream>
    <tags>skill, audit, cadence</tags>
    <estimate>45min</estimate>
    <rigor>FULL</rigor>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>060, 061, 062, 063, 064, 011</dependencies>
    <writes-to>.claude/skills/procedure-quality-audit/</writes-to>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    <goal>Single-entrypoint skill that runs all 4 validators + reference-exemplar tests + manual spot-check of 3 random opted-out skills + CLAUDE.md line-count check. Produces .claude/QUALITY-AUDIT-&lt;date&gt;.md.</goal>
    <context>This is the recurring entry point for the monthly cadence. Friction-minimal: one command produces one report.</context>
    <constraints>
      - Use the canonical skill template (.claude/skills/_template/SKILL.md)
      - Must have exemplar: field (likely none-too-volatile — the audit's output is the report itself)
      - Must have Gotchas section
    </constraints>
  </prompt>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/skills/_template/SKILL.md</file>
      <file>scripts/quality/Validate-ClaudeSettings.ps1</file>
      <file>scripts/quality/Find-PatternDrift.ps1</file>
      <file>scripts/quality/Test-ReferenceExemplars.ps1</file>
      <file>scripts/quality/Check-BundleSizeDrift.ps1</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step>Clone _template into .claude/skills/procedure-quality-audit/</step>
    <step>Write SKILL.md describing: when to invoke, what it runs, where output goes, how to interpret report</step>
    <step>Trigger phrases in description: "quality audit", "procedure audit", "run the audit", "monthly audit"</step>
    <step>What it runs: invokes scripts/quality/Run-ProcedureQualityAudit.ps1 (task 081)</step>
    <step>Output location: .claude/QUALITY-AUDIT-YYYY-MM-DD.md</step>
    <step>Gotchas section: known false positives (e.g., bundle-size threshold of 20% may flag legitimate growth), how to suppress</step>
    <step>References: link to each validator + the cadence doc (task 083)</step>
    <step>exemplar: none-too-volatile (the audit is meta — testing exemplars but not having its own)</step>
  </steps>

  <outputs>
    <output>.claude/skills/procedure-quality-audit/SKILL.md</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Skill follows template structure</criterion>
    <criterion>Invocation produces audit report</criterion>
    <criterion>Description triggers on intended phrases</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
